Hazelnut Spread Brownie Hack 🍫
where are my chocolate lovers at? This one is for you. Swap the hazelnut spread for peanut butter, almond butter or anything you’d like in the center of your brownies. By freezing the spread on parchment paper before baking, it allows the spread to be nice and gooey in the center rather than being absorbed by the brownie batter. This is a great trick 👌🏼 I made these for my cookie platter this year and they were a crowd favorite.
.
⭐️save this post for later~ follow @sailor_bailey for more!
.
What’s in it::
*Boxed brownie batter or click the link in my bio for my fave brownie recipe
* hazelnut spread like Nutella or peanut butter
*parchment or wax paper
Just cut the parchment paper, similar in size to the brownie pan you will be using. Spread hazelnut or peanut butter onto that parchment paper and then freeze it.
make your brownie batter lay half of it into the pan. Add the frozen spread layer and then dollop the leftover brownie batter over it. Bake, allow it to cool once finished and enjoy the gooey flavorful center!
.

Sheet Pan Baked Breakfast Quesadilla 🧀
No greasy fingers for this one! Feed a crowd or meal prep breakfast for the week. I won’t judge if you eat the whole thing yourself either 😉 this makes about 8 servings.

⭐️save this post for later~ follow @sailor_bailey for more

How to make::
10 Medium/large tortillas
12 eggs scrambled
1-2 cups of cheese
1 can of drained/rinsed black beans
Salt/pepper
Toppings: avocado, salsa, sour cream, sliced tomatoes, whatever you prefer.
.
*Preheat oven to 350° you will need two cooking sheets. Lay seven of the tortillas around the first cooking sheet. Make sure that they hang over the edge like they do in the video. 
*Add scrambled eggs, cheese, or any other add ins. Lay three of the tortillas down the center over the Mix in’s.
*Fold all of the tortillas into each other so they overlap is Tooth picks at the corners to keep it down.
grab parchment paper, pull tooth picks out and quickly lay the parchment paper over the folded tortillas. Lay second cooking sheet over that. Bake! *Bake for about 15-20 minutes be sure to check on it once the tortillas start to brown and crisp they are ready to go! Less grease more feasting!

How To Make::
Ingredients
4 eggs
2 tbsp oil (separated)
1⁄4 tsp salt
1⁄2 tsp pepper
2 tbsp crumbled feta
1⁄2 cup cooked quinoa
2 cups arugula
1.5 cup cherry tomatoes
2 tbsp balsamic vinegar
Additional (optional) toppings: avocado, pickled onions, roasted potatoes.
👉🏼Preheat oven on broil low. In a small 6x6 or similar in size oven safe ceramic dish, drizzle 1 tbsp of oil, add tomatoes and drizzle balsamic vinegar. Roast tomatoes for about 8-10 minutes or until lightly blistered. Set aside to cool and start the egg scramble.
👉🏼In a large bowl, add 4 eggs, salt, pepper, and feta. Whisk with a fork. Heat oil on medium/high in a medium sized skillet. Once it’s hot, pour eggs into skillet and put heat on low. Slowly stir the eggs with spatula until desired cook (about 2 minutes).
In a bowl, serve quinoa and arugula as the base, top with balsamic tomatoes, egg scramble and all other toppings of choice (avocado, pickled onions, potatoes, and any other toppings!)
